rComments: Probably the best Prof I've had this semester! Super sweet and caring! Assignments were on Wiley+ and were super easy! Midterms were fair as long as you did practise questions but final exam was difficult. Definitely recommend taking CHM1311 with him!

I had Sandro in the fall term, and he was honestly a very kind man. He knows what he is talking about, and you can tell he cares about his students and wants them to be successful. He responds to emails himself and is very fast and willing to work with you. He uses Wiley+, which allows five tries per question!
An actual KING. Legend. Very funny, nonchalant and nice. Easy course if you did well in CHM4U.

The W+ system was so nerve racking but he's a solid prof and responds quickly. While explaining the concepts he makes sure that you understand. Sometimes he stayed extra mins on zoom just to answer questions related to lectures and assignments. PROTECT HIM AT ALL COST. Just stay on track with him during lectures and you'll be fine.
He uses a software W+ where you get 5 attempts per question for the exam/midterms which was great. That means not part marks so that screwed me over. He over simplifies a lot which wasn't helpful.

If you have this and it is offered ONLINE by Sandro, TAKE IT! If you did well in 4U chem this class will be a lot of review. Hw and Exams were done on Wiley+, for exams we got 5 attempts per question (no part marks tho), and 3 attempts on the final. You kind of have to teach yourself but Sandro's section had the highest average because of attempts.

Dr. Gambarotta is an enthusiastic, caring, and all around great prof. Explains concepts well and is very good online. Assignments are made to help you learn. Tests are flexible with him correcting technical errors.
Anyone that gave low rating is just booty in chemistry. If you did really well in chemsitryu4 definitely take him.
He saved my long life dream to become a physician and potentially cure cancer. I love u Dr. Sandro.

Professor Gambarotta is amazing, there were many instances to raise your mark if you opted in for wiley+. He has a thick Italian accent so it is a bit difficult to understand him but his explanations for concepts are very good. He definitely knows his stuff. Only issue is with the light unit his slides are all theory but assignments are all math.

he has so much patience for student questions, goes over concepts thoroughly, and even gives marks just for practicing. assignments are very easy to do well on. on an online midterm, i wrote a number wrong but correct on paper. he still gave me the point. he does care about students and wants to see you succeed. one of my fav classes hands down.
His lectures are hilarious and there definitely is a learning curve which at the end of the day is worth it. Very kind and gives weekly assignments/practice which is useful.

In all honesty, Gambarotta's SUPER caring and hilarious. I have a learning accommodation and he always makes sure to email me to ensure everything is properly set up for exams. Also, he's super quick at replying and a chill dude. I agree his lectures are a little iffy as well as his accent but he's a decent teacher nonetheless. It's Chemistry, so..

Dr. Gambarotta is a very kind and genuine professor who is easy to approach and gives great feedback. That being said, this class is not for everybody as it is, for the most part, independent study. However, the lecture notes are all you need to succeed in this class. The midterm and final exam follow the lectures to the point and were fair.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: For a 4th year course, there was very little material covered. Most of it is just rehashing the prerequisites. Very boring and barely teaches. Made a lot of inappropriate jokes about suicide and COVID-19. I feel like I learned nothing and wasted a lot of time. One bright side is that it is the easiest 4th year chemistry course at uOttawa.

Sandro is one of the funniest professors here. He's like the best Italian grandpa you never had. Midterms were tough and the final was ridiculously long (almost no one could finish it) but with assignments, attendance marks and the generous lab grade, it's pretty hard to fail. Would recommend this guy! Also don't bother buying the textbook for this

Sandro is a hilarious professor. He makes his lectures fun and likes to explain how the stuff you learn will apply to real world application/future courses. Pretty easy A+, just show up to class, study and do the assignments. Pretty much an extension of grade 12 chemistry, doing mostly the same things with a bit of new topics!

This website is biased; people will rate a prof really good simply because they ended up with an A, this is the only reason he has a 3.0 (he boosts). Maybe you'll get an A but you will learn NOTHING. He spends his time going on tangents about industry and barely spends time on the type of questions you'll see. Do the Wiley, practice Q's in slides
Very good prof, many extra grades.
Very sweet man but terrible teacher. Just reads off the slides. Only teaches theory but tests on math. If you can get a different prof I would.

Very mixed feelings about this prof. At first, he is very hard to understand; however, you do adapt to it over time. He happens to be quite funny. His lecture slides are not useful, as the solutions to the examples shown are hard to follow. The hardest questions found on the Wiley Plus are usually also on midterms and the exam. Difficult overall.

I hate chem, and he didn't teach me anything. I ended this course more confused about chem then when I entered. He did not teach it well at all and his exams were out of such few marks that two or three mistakes really brought down your grade. Also has an accent, difficult to understand. Takes in class attendance.

Do yourself a favour and switch out of this class immediately. He reads off his slides the entire time, all of the homework and all of the examples on this slides are nothing compared to what you'll see on midterms and finals. his tests are weighted with 40% being 2 questions of the 9 so good luck getting anything higher than 65 on them. Horrible.

MANDATORY attendance. That's the only reason for going to class tbh. He reads off the slides and expects you to listen, understand, and takes notes all while he talks about a ridiculously fast pace. You're going to have to learn the course yourself. Go to class but do your own thing otherwise it'll just be a waste of your time.
He was literally the worst prof ever. You basically have to teach yourself. He was funny at times but overall was not good. I wouldn't recommend him and would never take his class again.

He is a good guy, he attempts to teach the class his best. IMO he was not the best professor, however he does care about the success of his students. If you do poorly on the midterms but better on the final, he will calculate your grade to see what gives you the highest mark. Try a dif. prof if possible. Exams are not like textbook questions.

If you have him, SWITCH OUT! His lectures aren't well organized and he's very boring and difficult to understand. It's essentially a self-taught course. He DOES NOT take his questions from the textbook anymore. WileyPLUS is optional but it's a good grade booster. I learned everything from the DGD - he's absolutely the worst chemistry teacher.

Really don't know how his rating isn't lower than 3.0. This man is singlehandedly responsible for my depression this semester. Orgo 1 sucks and I could not understand this guy in the lectures at all and fell asleep constantly. Only silver lining is that there were lots of free marks and tests were all textbook questions, which saved me in the end.

This course was definitely not easy but it wasn't hard to do really well in the class. Just do a bunch of the textbook questions because he takes questions from there for his tests. He isn't the best prof, but his exams were way easier than all the other profs. He gives you lots of opportunities to do well in the class since he has a 5% easy bonus.

not good at explaining things, is impatient, blames terrible course avgs on students, lies about what will be on midterms, tells you not to buy textbook then puts all textbook questions on the midterm, not taking orgo ever again bc of him :)

Decent teacher but explains in a mediocre way. He doesnt respect the order of the chapters compare to the other org chem teachers. I went to tutorial sessions and it was pointless, gambarotta doesnt teacher in the same order nor uses the same reagents. Good teacher for previous chm class but not excellent for organic chem. Heavy topics/bad explanat

Sandro is a really great prof. 2 midterms and an exam, attendance is marked everyday. Do they wiley+ assignments and go to the DGDs. Organic chem is a tough subject but he does a great job of explaining it and is clearly very passionate!

Sandro was an amazing prof. He makes his lectures interesting by simply showing that he's a fun guy who is enthusiastic about what he does. Definitely do all the online assignments as they're easy points and do a bunch of practice questions from the textbook and his resources on his website to do well.
Don't take his course, unless you want to drop university.

He's an energetic lecturer but a little bit hard to follow at first. He's a good prof but his questions on the midterms were tricky, not that they were hard but that the question itself was stated weirdly and was easy to lose marks if you interpreted it wrong BUT he does let you make up your marks which is always amazing!

Lectures are extremely boring and he just reads off his slides and essentially teaches you nothing. It's not worth going to class except for the fact that attendance is mandatory. FIrst midterm was alright, but the second midterm and exam were impossible. Despite all this, he's a pretty funny guy and means well.
Funny guy. Understanding human. Rather boring lectures. Turns the lights too low which make you sleepy. All in all, a good prof. Will take again.

Gave a good amount of free marks (attendance, boosted a letter grade, curves tests) all without asking, basically the reason I passed. Very nice teacher and caring, his tests are fair too chem is just a really hard subject for most regardless.

He doesn't know how to teach to properly. He expects you to just look at an example in his powerpoint and understand it within 2 seconds. Teaching method just did not work for me. The final was way to long, it was 26 questions long with 26 pages, barely anyone finished their exam properly. But his midterms are pretty fair
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Get ready to read', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: Sandro was a very interesting prof to listen to. He is very energetic and enthusiastic about the course. An issue with him is concerning how he taught where he just really read calculations and steps in his slides which means you will have to go back and review it. He is very helpful with understanding concepts. His examinations are also fair.

Sandro is always in a good mood, very energetic. Super accessible outside class, responds to emails within an hour. He does tons of examples. Gives bonus questions on midterms. Study for midterms from past midterms and tutorials posted on his website.
Great prof! very energetic and consistently keeps you up to date on bright space!
I don't know how to say about this professor, he does not really teach you anything  in class, you have to learn by yourself.

Dr. Gambarotta is hilarious. I love reading his emails because they are WILD. He's not the best prof ever, but he's laid back and his tests are pretty easy with lots of bonus questions. Also, he doesn't test you on the lab skills (which is a HUGE plus). My advice is to practice the mechanisms, and do his old midterms that he posts.

Extremely sweet, and gives a lot of free marks. He can be a bit hard to understand sometimes because he really goes in depth with the topics and they can get confusing, especially for the mechanisms. Midterms are short and fairly easy--lots of multiple choice. Overall, extremely caring and really cares about his students.

Overall I think he's a good prof. His lectures are not boring so its easy to keep attentive in class but sometimes his teaching is not as clear as it could be. He's quite approachable and usually answers your question on the spot, however if you send him an email, his responses are quite vague and don't fully answer the question asked.

Sandro is such a great prof! He explains things very well and is incredibly approachable after class if you have any questions. Likes to use WileyPlus very often. Work load consists of pre-lecture quizzes, post lecture assignments, 2 midterms, and a final. Super nice guy!

Cares about his students passing. To pass, just do assignments - they're mostly online and match exams given. He teaches great and he's funny, just catching up is hard because LOTS of material to cover. Easy A if you know what you're doing. I just didn't study hard enough for his class
He is really good.

Really wants students to succeed and will shift marks on midterms and finals. Gives almost 15% in free marks with online assignments and tests. Lab portion worth very little which is frustrating but still do the work. Gives lots of practice from past exams and do all of them and you will do amazing on the final. Pay attention and take notes.

Great professor. Very easy class! He gives students a lot of bonuses and his marking scheme is very easy to do well. I ended up with an A + in the course because the material on the exams were very similar to the practice one he gave to students online. Would recommend taking 1331 with him anyway.

Had him for CHM1311 and again for CHM1321 because I loved him that much. His marking scheme is so generous (especially for CHM1321) you get marks for everything. Do the practice questions on Sapling and the practice exams. Hilarious, kind, adorable old man who makes chemistry tolerable. TAKE HIM IF YOU CAN YOU WONT REGRET IT
Great teacher! Explains organic chemistry in a fun and helpful way. Lots of time available for office hours and I'm telling you, SANDRO wants each and every student to succeed.
Lectures are long, boring and hard to follow
Don't do it. He teaches chemistry entirely off of a powerpoint ...

Super nice and very funny. Keeps you engaged and reserves the class before the midterms for review sessions. His Sapling assignments are an easy 10% and you only need 50% to get full marks in the homework section.

Great professor, some people don't like his lecture style but his power points are super helpful and give you an exact outline of how to do specific calculations. He gives you many examples and lots of resources. You get 5% for attending class, and you get 10% for easy online assignments. Adds lots of extra marks. Cares about students.

In class he can be a bit confusing, but overall he wants students to succeed. He let the class replace their midterm marks with final exam marks if they were higher, so it is really easy to get a good mark. All of his questions are recycled from previous years for the most part.

Dr. Gambarotta does operate the baseline of his lectures off his posted course powerpoint. The key is to participate in class, because when you do, he goes into detail and works it out in person; additionally, the level of help he will go to if you ask of it in person is immense. If I take more chemistry courses, I will be looking for his name.

I've never given a prof a bad review and am an A student. I failed this course. Very boring & unclear,  doesn't  cover all of the material necessary for the exam. In fact, he didn't manage to get through everything so had to learn last 2 chpters on our own. The final was 3x longer than other classes and avg. was failing grade. AVOID THIS PROF!!!

Decent prof, very passionate and helpful, but not very good lectures (really bad powerpoints). Attendance is marked, and the online assignments are pretty easy. Doesn't use Blackboard for some reason. However, Orgo I is a pretty tough class. Know your nomenclature; it won't be taught. A word of advice: don't take the class if you don't need to.

final was 30 long answer questions when the other section had 7.. horrible lecturer. found myself being thankful that the lectures were mandatory because that was an easy 5%. assignments are easy and a mark booster
Can't convey anything properly. Classes were a chore to go to cause they were mandatory. I would say to choose anyone but him.

Very nice and really wants you t succeed.  Not always the clearest at explaining things but his powerpoints really help. If you go over the homework and all the practice midterms before the exam you`re guaranteed to pass.

He appeared to skip over some of the stuff which is required from Orgo II, but nothing that can not be looked over and understood in 10 minutes. Over alright prof, very helpful at office hours and quite nice.

Great prof, the attendance is mandatory but helps a lot. His midterms and exams are so easy. They reflect the types of questions during his lecture slides perfectly, with some repeating themselves on tests. Tips to for an A or better his class: study his slides not the textbook, understand why reactions happen and don't just memorize.

Good prof, a lot of the ratings on here say otherwise but really all you need to do is attend class and listen, if you do that then you'll be fine. Exams reflect the class material and are pretty easy.
sucks, final was 30 question long when others was only 7 questions. very rude during office hours but nice and funny during lectures.

Really a great prof! He gets a lot of flack, but his classes are really interesting (for a first year class). He's great in his office hours so if you need help, go to him. His lecture slides can be a little vague so make sure to do textbook reading on your own.
He's hilarious and really cares about helping you do well. Definitely recommend for 1311, but avoid for 1321! Probably my favorite prof first semester.

Very enthusiastic and passionate prof. He may have issues drilling concepts into people's minds - but that's because they don't practice. Do the MasteringChem questions and ones from the book! Like math, organic chem takes alot of practice to build understanding and confidence. 1-on-1, Gambarotta is crystal clear. Go seek help when you need it!

He really tries his best at conveying the matter. Doesn't always get through though.  Lots of analogies and complicated examples.  Just do lots of practice questions in preparation for the midterms and final, as they were very different than what was taught in the class.  Average.
Very enthusiastic

Awful lecturer. He is all over the map, and his powerpoint slides are not clear whatsoever. However his midterms AND final exam were multiple choice, made everything easier. Just remember to do the practice midterms over and over; he recycles a lot of the questions, especially for the final.
Both his midterms and exam were multiple choice. He wasn't very clear, but he really cared about his students. Go to a different profs lecture and use the textbook.

He does many things to help you make up for poor midterm marks but since he's awful at teaching, you wont do so well on the midterms (2nd one will destroy you). So, to sum it up, he's helpful mark-wise (not saying you'll do well) but he's awful at teaching.

Really nice and funny guy! He does his best to keep the class interesting but let's face it: this IS organic chem. Not always the best at explaining concepts so you need to study hard. Midterms are tricky and do not always reflect what you learned in class. Sometimes it seems like we're just expected to know something on our own. Good luck!
Midterms not like his teachings.you can study hard and understand the material, but still do bad
Get out of his class!

I liked him. He cares about the students.  His problem is lecturing to the class. One on one he is very helpful. You have to study a lot. He likes to trick you on midterms. Its unfair because if you study really hard and seem to understand the material, you could still end up with a poor grade.
Great guy, more than willing to help clarify at all times and is trying to make bland material fun. It's easy to tell he actually cares about all his students.

Class of 09. He does not teach anything that is useful or will actually help you understand the material. Albeit he tries to make us understand it using funny analogies. The final was very difficult compared to midterms. He asks specific questions that require a small single sentence answer from a 1400 page book. The book is useless at an exam.

He's a nice person, but teaching doesn't seem to be his thing. I recommend you going to his office hours because he seems very open to help you out. Sometimes I think there is a language barrier and doesn't seem to understand our questions. Go to DGDs, and do MasteringChem to help yourself out.
READ TEXTBOOK and do mastering chem. hes a nice guy but he can't teach.

Switch to Dr. Flynn or Ogilvie now! You've been warned... =P No honestly.. he doesn't cover mechanisms which you will be in trouble when you take organic II (when the profs actually cover mechanisms in depth...) For CHM1311, he is fine though!
Multiple choice open book exams. He gave everyone 10% boost on final and midterm because so many people failed them. for org chem he does not teach mechanisms which kills your for org 2!
you're better off if you study on your own... even though exams are open book, they're a lot harder than they should be!
Worst teacher on campus. If you get him switch into any other section that he is not teaching. Covers no basics. Open book tests were much much harder then they sound

For General Chem, he's actually pretty good.  Everything was clear, and he went through everything in depth.  DO THE PRACTICE ON MASTERCHEMISTRY!  His midterms were easy (for us no MC), but somehow the exam was way different from what the midterms were.  Either way in general everything was good.  Just DON'T get him for organic chem!

Not a good lecturer, doesn't stress important details, multiple choice open book exams/midterms are brutal.  So far the only class I stopped attending and self-taught myself out of the textbook.  Don't know how I did in the course yet, but I know I didn't do well.  If you're set to be in his class, SWITCH NOW!

Does not stress the most important part of organic - mechanisms - and I was lost all semester because he didn't cover the  basics in the first few classes. Funny and friendly, but will not teach you what you need to know! Despite what other raters might say, multiple choice tests are hard when you aren't properly taught how everything works.

If your not gonna take Orgo2, take his class. With multiple choice open book exams, your basically guaranteed a good mark. I didnt study for the final at all and got an A+. Unfortunately, if your planning on taking orgo2, avoid this class. Either you'll fail or struggle. You wont even know how to do the most basic part of organic-Mechanisms!
OOh Sandro!....Sandro is a nice guy. Great accent! Nice illustrations!....lecture slides are always repeated and disorganised but ooh well...he's still great!

Multiple Choice Mid-Terms are retarded. He thinks he's helping us but he's only digging us a deeper hole for Orgo 2. Id rather a normal midterm and write out the mechanisms than try and pick the best one of 5 off a sheet :S
No Comments
The only thing good about him is he made an insanely easy exam. No comment on his teaching.
No Comments

Oh Sandro, you so crazy.  Great guy but I found his class pretty hard.  He really tries to explain things well but I found I didn't understand what he was saying a lot of the time and b/c of this I would lose interest.  You can do well in this class but you have to be willing to put in effort to learn from the text etc, I wasn't and I suffered.
You will not learn enough in this class.  You are better off in the other section to be prepared for second year organic chem, even if you get a lower mark.

He uses great analogies to explain the material, making it very clear and easy to understand. His accent is great, but kind of hard to understand when you can barely hear him. Wears his pants really high too.
Great teacher... overall a nice guy.  Funny, but in a way to help you to understand organic chem better.  His exams were awesome, no suprises.  Strongly recommend this teacher.
Talks like super mario :)

VERY funny.. accent, appearance, explanations! sometimes his slides are out of order and/or repeated but overall course very good. he should teach mechanisms though. his midterm is HARD but exam is super easy... i failed the midterm but still managed an A+!!!
No Comments
"It's a fantasy!" The guy has a strong accent.. very hard to understand when he teached the french section..
Funny and helpful
Great prof, very interesting course. Midterm and final are fair :)
No Comments
Very fair, wants everyone to do well. Never got angry and always had a sense of humour. He's great!
Funny Guy, Funny Explanation. Very hard course, I'm suprised I passed, mayeb it's because he's a pretty good prof :)
Funny teacher, tries his best to teach a 300 student class. Course is extremely hard, lot's of work. He tried his best to make it easy.
I *love* Gambie! He made me want to do chemistry.  At the end of the story  this guy kicks ass.
